        160
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## How the Image-to-Slide Process Works\n\nüîÑ **How Images Are Added to Slides** \n1.  The workflow fetches all images (that pass the filter) from your specified Google Drive folder.\n2.  It sorts these images by their creation date.\n3.  For each image, the workflow:\n    a. Creates a new blank slide in your Google Slides presentation.\n    b. Updates the image's permissions in Google Drive to be publicly readable (this is a temporary step, necessary for the Google Slides API to insert the image using its URL).\n    c. Adds the image to the new slide, fitting it to the slide's dimensions.\n\n**Final Touch:** After all images are added, the *very first slide* of the presentation (which is a blank page from your template) is deleted.",
        "height": 340,
        "width": 840,
        "color": 6
      },
